latestIgtvVideos.title: What to do after COVID vaccine.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here are a few things to keep in mind after getting the COVID vaccine. 
Also: remember no alcohol one day before or after the vaccine. Pregnant and breastfeeding moms should check with their docs. I did and mine told me to get it. 
Fever can be treated with a basic paracetamol. There will be some numbness and soreness at the sight of vaccine for a few days. Nothing unmanageable. But yep, it will be sore. Don’t ice it (that’s what our doc advised). It will heal in a weeks time. 
Just please get vaccinated — humble request to all. 

Stay safe. 
Xo,
S.

Remember when Avicii said, ‘Live a life you will remember’? This was ours—sun-kissed skin, salt in the air, belly laughs, barefoot joy. Maldives gave us moments we’ll play on repeat. 🌊☀️💙 

#FamilyEdition

Details : 
We stayed at @luxsouthari - a simply stunning luxurious resort in a private island. It’s an ideal vacation for families or couples who want to unwind and relax before the summer break ends, spend sometime tog with the kids and as a couple without any agenda or lists. That’s all we wanted from this trip - a No Agenda, No Itinerary, No Plan kinda week. And we got just that in the best possible way here. 

Budget - 12-15L (including flight tickets - ours was slightly more since we had to book tickets from RPR-BOM both ways and book hotels there too for 1 night. It will vary depending on your flight seat,  room and meal plan, activities, spa etc. 

1. The villas - superior and huge! We had one with the pvt pool and beach.. water villas are smaller in size and if you are travelling with kids - choose the beach villas. Way bigger and more fun. 
2. The food - OMG decadent!! They have multiple multi cuisines restaurants- each better than the last. I mean come on… I ate more in a day than i do in 3 days.. still didn’t feel like I overate. Freshest seafood( we had lobsters, grilled crabs, crab cakes , all kinda shrimps, calamari, fish, octopus, oysters (the BEST)! extremely decadent desserts and a huge variety from indian to Thai, Japanese, authentic Italian, pan Asian and more. Dreamy! Do NOT miss ICI - the ice cream bar. The drinks menu is great! We had drinks for every meal I think 🤣 The dinners by the beach were so good.. beautiful breeze, kids happy, us - happy. What more does one want? 
3. Water sports - great range! Pick and choose but def do.. snorkel, parasail, jet ski, kayak - all awesome! Go on the dolphin cruise, and walks along the beach. 
4. Spa & Sauna - luxurious and ultimate! 

All I can say is I already miss #maldives and wish I could go back again next month! One place ticked off our list! Next up - Alaska!

POV: You finally slowed down.

No rush. No schedule. Just warm sand, a sky full of moods, and the sound of the sea reminding you to exhale.

This wasn’t a trip to escape life — it was to remember how beautiful it can be when you’re not rushing through it.

From salty hair to soul-deep calm, Maldives… you are magic. 🌴🌊
